<item>
            <title>[SPARK-21414] Buffer in SlidingWindowFunctionFrame could be big though window is small</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-21414</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;tt&gt;SlidingWindowFunctionFrame&lt;/tt&gt;, it is now adding all rows to the buffer for which the input row value is equal to or less than the output row upper bound, then drop all rows from the buffer for which the input row value is smaller than the output row lower bound.&lt;br/&gt;
This could result in the buffer is very big though the window is small. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example: &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;select a, b, sum(a) over (partition by b order by a range between 1000000 following and 1000001 following) from table&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
